HEADWORD: Farctate
<hw>Farc"tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>farctus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>farcire</ets>. See <er>Farce</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Stuffed; filled solid;
<as>as, a <ex>farctate</ex> leaf, stem, or pericarp</as>; -- opposed to
<xex>tubular</xex> or <xex>hollow</xex>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

